Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Lamb & Lentil Curry, Rice & Spinach in just 20 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

== Turmeric Rice ==

Bring a large #saucepan{} of @water{100%ml} to the boil with @salt{0.25%tsp}. When boiling, add the @basmati rice{150%g} and half the @ground turmeric{½%tsp}, cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Drain in a #sieve{}.

== Lamb Curry ==

Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). When the pan is hot, add the @lamb mince{200%g} and cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces).

Once the lamb has browned, stir the onion into the pan with the lamb and cook, stirring, until the onion is starting to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}.

While the onion cooks, halve the @red chilli{½}(halved lengthways, deseeded and finely chopped), peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%200g pack} in a sieve.

Once the onion has softened, add the @North Indian style spice mix{1%tbsp}, garlic and half the chilli and remaining turmeric and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @tomato passata{1%250g jar}, water and @chicken stock powder{1%tsp} to the pan and stir together. Stir in the lentils, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, add a pinch of @sugar{pinch} and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if you feel it needs loosening.

== Spinach ==

Add the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time and cook until wilted and piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

== To Serve ==

Divide the turmeric rice between #bowls{}. Top with the curry and any remaining chilli. Enjoy!